**✅ Level 3 — Production Grade Helm Chart**

Maintenant Chartt `broapp` sera plu profesional, reusable, et aprocher env prod.

---

### **Level 3 Goals:**

- Créer **Library Chart** (common helpers)
- Ajouter `values.schema.json` (validation values)
- Ajouter `affinity`, `tolerations`, `nodeSelector` (très important dans AKS)
- Utiliser `tpl` function pour plus dymamique
- plus propre et scalable

---

### l'étape est:

#### 1. Créer Library Chart (le plus important)

Créer le repo et le fichier:

```bash
mkdir -p broapp/charts/common/templates
```

**File:** `broapp/charts/common/Chart.yaml`
```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: common
description: Common library chart for broapp
type: library
version: 0.1.0
```

**File:** `broapp/charts/common/templates/_helpers.tpl`

```yaml
{{- define "common.labels" -}}
helm.sh/chart: {{ include "common.chart" . }}
{{ include "common.selectorLabels" . }}
app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}
{{- end }}

{{- define "common.selectorLabels" -}}
app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include "common.name" . }}
app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}
{{- end }}

{{- define "common.name" -}}
{{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}

{{- define "common.chart" -}}
{{- printf "%s-%s" .Chart.Name .Chart.Version | replace "+" "_" | trunc 63 | trimSuffix "-" }}
{{- end }}

{{- define "common.image" -}}
{{- printf "%s:%s" .Values.image.repository .Values.image.tag }}
{{- end }}
```

#### 2. Update `Chart.yaml` (à root repo broapp)

```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: broapp
description: Advanced Helm Chart soi-meme - Production Ready
type: application
version: 0.2.0
appVersion: "1.0.0"
dependencies:
  - name: common
    version: 0.1.0
    repository: file://./charts/common
```

#### 3. Update `values.yaml` (Ajouter ce value )

Ajouter ces lignes le plus en bas de ce fichier  `values.yaml`:

```yaml
# AKS Specific Configuration
nodeSelector: {}
tolerations: []
affinity: {}

# Environment specific
environment: production

# Azure Workload Identity (On utlilisera)
workloadIdentity:
  enabled: false
  clientId: ""

# Schema validation will be enforced
```

#### 4. Créer le fichier validation : `values.schema.json`

créer ce ficher dans le root folder `broapp/`:

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "replicaCount": {
      "type": "integer",
      "minimum": 1
    },
    "image": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "repository": { "type": "string" },
        "tag": { "type": "string" }
      },
      "required": ["repository", "tag"]
    },
    "resourcePreset": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["small", "medium"]
    },
    "ingress": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "enabled": { "type": "boolean" },
        "host": { "type": "string" }
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["image", "resourcePreset"]
}
```

